subject: zs1lt6vf
complexity_strategy:
If I can't find a pattern and there's not many of blank spaces, I'll rate it as high complexity.
If I can find a pattern, even if there's not much of blank space, I'll rate it in the middle.
If I can find a pattern, and there're many blank spaces (either mainly black or white), I'll rate it as low complexity.
most_complex: The QR code like patterns were the most complex to me.
complexity difference: There was, because I believe the complete image will show a pattern, while the important parts have been grayed out for the visible image.

subject: shyjmfof
complexity_strategy: intuition

complexity difference: yes- my brain tried to forecast the gaps to be filled in similar patterns to the visual I was given.

subject: gv15r07r

subject: jczjooq8

subject: qrv5tnhj
complexity_strategy: I tried to think about if I thought that the pattern seemed to be one that would simply mirror itself in the gray area or if the pattern was so different that it would be impossible to just guess how the marks in the hidden gray spots would look.
most_complex: The most complex ones changed for me as the game went on. I began to view the ones with little pattern and more random spots as being more complex and unpredictable, rather than complex ones just being ones with more detailing.
complexity difference: A bit. Usually I feel like my ratings stayed someone similar to one another. But, sometimes, if a pattern was one where most of the square was gray, I would place the imagined rating higher because I had no idea how the rest of the image would look if I could see past the gray.
